node.text:
Hola amigos! This month we are celebrating our Hispanic Heritage!🎉As part of the celebration, we’ve partnered up to help you bring some amazing books into your classroom that celebrate our Hispanic/Latinx heritage and culture with an Amazon gift card!📚To enter, just follow these easy steps:

🌟Like & save this post & comment with your favorite children’s book.
🌟Go to @teacherslovebooksgiveaway
and follow the directions on there!

And that’s it! You’ve entered!🎉

node.text: GUESS WHAT! I have a new neighbor! @texaslonestarteacher is teaching down the hall! My campus was in need of a new 5th grade ELA teacher, so I put in a good word for this pretty cool girl I know, who also happens to be brilliant and creative in the classroom. Shoutout to my principal for trusting my recommendation because we snagged an amazing teacher! #omgiknowher #coyotes #teachingbuddies #texasteachersofinstagram #teachersofinstagram #teachersfollowteachers #iteach3rd #thirdistheword #smallworld

node.text:
The return of Barry the Base Ten Man!!! Understanding base ten relationships and the power of ten as an 8 year old is kind of like understanding how to do your own taxes as a thirty-something year old. So enter Barry! First we describe and identify the names of the blocks (units, rods, flats, and cubes), discuss the digits and values that make up his face, and then explore ways to rename those numbers based on groups of ten. For example, the value of Barry’s nose is 1,000, which is the same as 10 hundreds or 100 rods. It mostly blows their minds 🤪, but we’re making progress! You can find Barry here 👉🏼 https://bit.ly/BarryTheBaseTenMan 
**Magnetic base ten blocks from @lakeshorelearning** #barrythebasetenman #iteachthird #thirdistheword #placevalue #basetenblocks #teachersofinstagram #teachersfollowteachers #mybrainhurts

node.text: Establishing voice levels up in here! We talked about each voice level, the mini humans provided examples of where and when each level is appropriate, and then we practiced what they sounds like. Quick, easy, and purposeful!  Shoutout to @pearceinprimary for the sticky note sorting idea! #voicelevels #thirdistheword #handsonlearning #iteachthird #teachersfollowteachers #teachersofinstagram #itsloudupinhere

node.text:
DIY DRY ERASE CLIPBOARD TUTORIAL!
1️⃣ Cut dry erase contact paper the length of a clipboard
2️⃣ Peel away backside of the contact paper 
3️⃣ Place sticky side of contact paper on the backside of the clipboard and smooth out any air bubbles
4️⃣ Trim excess paper using a utility knife
5️⃣ Paint and decorate the front side of the clipboard
